\subsection{[[HttpState]]}

%claude:
[[HttpState]] is what \verb+http.c+ in [[webfs]] keeps for each in-flight request.
It holds the network file descriptor, a buffered reader [<Ibuf>] (so headers
can be parsed line by line without one [[read]] per byte), and three out-
parameters that the response parser fills in: a captured \verb+Location+ for
redirects, captured \verb+Set-Cookie+ headers to forward to
\verb+webcookies+, and captured \verb+WWW-Authenticate+ challenges.

<<struct [[HttpState]](webfs)>>=
struct HttpState
{
    fdt fd;
    Ibuf b;
    Client *c;

    // fields filled by the response parser
    char *location;
    char *setcookie;
    char *credentials;

    <<[[HttpState]](webfs) other fields>>
};
@

%XXX
<<[[HttpState]](webfs) other fields>>=
char *netaddr;
char autherror[ERRMAX];
@


\subsection{[[Ibuf]]}

%claude:
[<Ibuf>] is a 4~KiB single-reader buffer wrapped around an [<Ioproc>]
descriptor. It exists so the response parser can do \verb+readline+-style
work without one [[read]] syscall per character. The same struct is shared
by the HTTP and FTP back-ends.

<<struct [[Ibuf]](webfs)>>=
/* simple buffered i/o for network connections; shared by http, ftp */
struct Ibuf
{
    fdt fd;
    Ioproc *io;
    char buf[4096];
    // read and write pointer in buf
    char *rp, *wp;
};
@

<<function [[initibuf]](webfs)>>=
void
initibuf(Ibuf *b, Ioproc *io, fdt fd)
{
    b->fd = fd;
    b->io = io;
    b->rp = b->wp = b->buf;
}
@


\subsection{[[Client]]}

%claude:
[[Client]] is the per-connection state of [[webfs]]: one of these for
every \verb+/mnt/web/N/+ directory currently open. The fields divide into
three groups.
%
The URLs (\verb+url+, \verb+baseurl+) and control settings
(\verb+ctl+) are configured by writes to \verb+ctl+.
%
The body and headers
(\verb+contenttype+, \verb+postbody+, \verb+redirect+, \verb+authenticate+)
are filled in once the response arrives. The plumbing
(\verb+creq+, \verb+io+, \verb+iobusy+, \verb+ref+) keeps a dedicated I/O
thread alive across the long network round-trip.

<<struct [[Client]](webfs)>>=
struct Client
{
    // URls and control settings
    Url *url;
    Url *baseurl;
    Ctl ctl;

    // filled once the response arrives
    char *contenttype;
    char *postbody;
    char *redirect;
    char *authenticate;

    // Plumbing
    Channel *creq;      /* chan(Req*) */
    Ioproc *io;
    int iobusy;
    int ref;

    <<[[Client]](webfs) other fields>>
};
@

