%claude:
[[convert]] is the master table of every encoding tcs knows about. The
rows fall into two flavours by the \verb+Table+ vs \verb+Func+ flag.
\verb+Table+ rows are static 256-entry maps from byte to Rune, used by
[<intable()>] / [<outtable()>]; this is enough for every single-byte
encoding (8859-X, KOI-8, Windows code pages, Mac Roman, EBCDIC). Other
rows are \verb+Func+ pairs: one for from-direction, one for
to-direction, each pointing at a stateful converter (Big~5, GB,
Shift-JIS, UTF-16, etc.). Adding a new encoding is one row plus its
table or function pair.

